# ðŸ”¢ MNIST Digit Recognition using CNN

This project implements a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to accurately recognize handwritten digits (0â€“9) using the MNIST dataset.

---

## ðŸ“Š Dataset

The MNIST dataset contains:
- 60,000 training images
- 10,000 testing images
- All images are **28x28 grayscale**, representing digits 0 to 9

Each image is labeled with the correct digit it represents.

---

## ðŸŽ¯ Project Objective

Build a deep learning model that:
- Takes a 28x28 pixel image as input
- Uses Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs)
- Classifies the digit with high accuracy (>98%)

---

## ðŸ§  CNN Architecture

```text
Input: 28x28 grayscale image â†’ reshaped to (28, 28, 1)

Layer 1: Conv2D(32 filters, 3x3 kernel, ReLU)
Layer 2: MaxPooling2D(2x2)
Layer 3: Conv2D(64 filters, 3x3 kernel, ReLU)
Layer 4: MaxPooling2D(2x2)
Layer 5: Flatten()
Layer 6: Dense(128, ReLU)
Output : Dense(10, Softmax) â†’ One for each digit class (0â€“9)
